The paper proposes a novel attention mechanism to enhance Convolutional Neural Networks for fine-grained recognition, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed mechanism involves learning to attend to lower-level feature activations, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed mechanism in terms of parameters and computation required, which is a common concern in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on gender recognition and food recognition tasks, which are common topics in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Wide Residual Networks, which is a common architecture in neural networks (cs.NE).
